  "prompt": "How much does an IAS earn in hand for services?",
  "response": "The in-hand salary of an Indian Administrative Service (IAS) officer varies depending on their rank and years of service. Here's a general idea of the salaries:\n\n1. **Entry-Level (Junior Time Scale) - Assistant Commissioner/Assistant Collector**\n   - Basic Pay: Approx. \u20b956,100\n   - Net Salary (after deductions like Provident Fund, Income Tax, etc.): Around \u20b950,000 - \u20b955,000.\n\n2. **Senior Time Scale - Additional District Magistrate (ADM)/Additional Deputy Commissioner**\n   - Basic Pay: Approx. \u20b967,700\n   - Net Salary: Around \u20b960,000 - \u20b965,000.\n\n3. **Junior Administrative Grade - District Magistrate/Deputy Commissioner**\n   - Basic Pay: Approx. \u20b978,800\n   - Net Salary: Around \u20b970,000 - \u20b975,000.\n\n4. **Selection Grade - DM/DC after 8 years of Service**\n   - Basic Pay: Approx. \u20b91,18,500\n   - Net Salary: Around \u20b91,00,000 - \u20b91,10,000.\n\n5. **Super Time Scale - Divisional Commissioner**\n   - Basic Pay: Approx. \u20b91,44,200\n   - Net Salary: Around \u20b91,20,000 - \u20b91,30,000.\n\n6. **Above Super Time Scale - Principal Secretary**\n   - Basic Pay: Approx. \u20b91,82,200\n   - Net Salary: Around \u20b91,50,000 - \u20b91,60,000.\n\n7. **Apex Scale - Chief Secretary**\n   - Basic Pay: Approx. \u20b92,05,400\n   - Net Salary: Around \u20b91,70,000 - \u20b91,80,000.\n\n8. **Cabinet Secretary**\n   - Basic Pay: \u20b92,50,000\n   - Net Salary: Around \u20b92,00,000 and above.\n\nThe in-hand salary can be affected by various allowances and factors such as HRA (House Rent Allowance), DA (Dearness Allowance), TA (Travel Allowance), and other benefits. It's also worth noting that IAS officers receive various perks such as official residences, vehicles, and other facilities which enhance their overall compensation package.",
